snippet: Fig. 19, a dim spot tucked behind the bright white walls of the Envoy Enterprises gallery, opens on the Lower East Side.
lead_paragraph: BACK in the early 2000s, a lounge called Passerby blurred the line between gallery and bar. Attached to Gavin Brown’s Enterprise gallery in Chelsea, it drew cool, artsy patrons who might have gone to an opening at the gallery earlier that night.

abstract: The bride is a foreign affairs analyst in Washington, the bridegroom an international trade counsel.

lead_paragraph: Meghan Elizabeth Giulino and Paul Henry DeLaney III were married Saturday at the St. Albans School’s chapel on the grounds of the National Cathedral in Washington. The Rev. William P. Billow, Jr., an Episcopal priest and the former senior chaplain of St. Albans, performed the ceremony.
